{"cursor":"16385","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn a 'support group', members provide each other with various types of help,\nusually nonprofessional and nonmaterial, for a particular shared, usually\nburdensome, characteristic. The help may take the form of providing and\nevaluating relevant information, relating personal experiences, listening to and\naccepting others' experiences, providing sympathetic understanding and\nestablishing social networks. A support group may also work to inform the public\nor engage in advocacy.\n","linknr":218,"url":"Support_group","recorded":1362535151,"links":18,"instances":[],"pdf":["http://eprints.ucl.ac.uk/archive/00001406/01/Online_support_groups.pdf","http://eprints.ucl.ac.uk/archive/00001406/01/Online_support_groups.pdf"],"categories":["Aftermath of war","Support groups|*","Self care","Types of organization","Personal development","Grief"],"headings":["History","Maintaining contact","Management by peers or professionals","Types of support groups","Online support groups","Support groups in popular media","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Parkins%28on%29line.png/220px-Parkins%28on%29line.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Social_network","Fraternal_organization","Freemasonry","Family","Trade_union","On-line_and_off-line","Hospitals","Drug_treatment","Prison","Disease","Cultural_identity","Public_relations","Mental_Health","Mensa_International","Gay_pride","Cult","Addiction_recovery_groups","AIDS","Alzheimer's","Alcoholics_Anonymous","Anxiety_disorder","Asperger_syndrome","Breastfeeding","Stroke","Brain_injury","Cancer_support_group","Circ